# Frontend React Core Rules

## Project Structure (New Projects)

- `pages/<PageName>.js` — one file per page
- `components/<PageName>/` — section components (Hero.js, Hero.css, Services.js, Services.css)
- `components/Shared/` — reusable components (Modal, Layout)
- `hooks/` — custom hooks used by 2+ components
- `public/<pageName>/` — page-specific assets

**Existing projects**: Never change folder structure. Follow project's patterns (routing, styling, state). Apply coding rules only.

## Page Rules

- Pages only structure layout; components handle design and logic
- Keep pages under ~100 lines
- One route per page component

```jsx
function Home() {
  return (
    <>
      <Hero />
      <Services />
      <Testimonials />
    </>
  );
}
```

## Component Rules

- One component = one UI section
- Each component has its own CSS file
- Keep components under ~150 lines; split if larger
- Naming: `PascalCase.js` (Hero.js), hooks `useToggle.js`, CSS `Hero.css`

## BEM-Style Class Naming

Use scoped names to avoid conflicts: `<page>-<section>__element`

```css
/* ✅ GOOD */
.home-hero { }
.home-hero__title { }
.services-card__title { }

/* ❌ BAD - conflicts across components */
.title { }
.button { }
.container { }
```

## Responsiveness (Tailwind + CSS)

- **Tailwind** for layout and responsive behavior
- **Custom CSS** for animations and complex styling
- Mobile first: `text-lg md:text-xl lg:text-3xl`
- Breakpoints: default (mobile), `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Container: `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4`
- Grid: `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6`

## Public Assets

- Page assets: `public/<pageName>/` (e.g. `public/home/`)
- Shared assets: `public/` or `public/assets/`
- Usage: `<img src="/home/hero-image.png" alt="Descriptive text" />`

## Accessibility

- Semantic HTML: `section`, `header`, `nav`, `main`, `article`, `footer`
- Meaningful `alt` text (not generic like "Hero")
- Keyboard accessible: use `<a>` or `<button>`, not `<div>` for controls
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
